This was my first time making gingerbread and it turned out pretty good! i read most of the comments and modified the recipe accordingly: X4 all spices, substituted ground cloves with allspice, used fresh ginger, 1/2 cup of molasses, coffee with the hot water. i used a magic bullet since i didn't have a mixer and mixed the wet and dry ingredients by hand. Cooked it for 30 minutes. Pretty good for a first try. thanks for all the tips everyone!

Rating: 3
Great taste, but I added much more spice than it called for (without really measuring). Also, I baked it for a good 20 minutes longer than it called for. After 30, it was still jiggling when I took it out of the oven. As an excellent low- fat alternative, I substituted apple sauce for the oil and it still tastes great!

