Rating: 4
This was great! Really light and moist. I made it with friends for a class party, and we served it with whipped cream and strawberries. Next time I think I'll add crystallized ginger. Excellent all around, and it smells amazing.

Rating: 3
Company coming in two hours and no butter (much less oatmeal stout). This recipe was a godsend. I used 1 cup whole wheat flour; 1 1/2 cup white, 1" piece of fresh ginger as I was out of powdered, black treacle as I was out of molasses, and ancho chili powder (1/2t) for amusement, as well as the coffee. Baked it for between 45 and 50 minutes to get it done (checked at 40 and it was close, but not done). People are correct that this is a light rather than dense cake, but it came out light as a feather and melted in the mouth. Praise all round; I am definitely going to make it again.

Rating: 2
