Rating: 2
I jacked up the spices on this one (four tablespoons ginger, two tablespoons cinnamon, one teaspoon cloves, 1/2 teaspoon allspice, and two tablespoons nutmeg) by personal preference. I cut the finished cake into squares, and dipped into a quick powdered sugar fondant (like with petit-fours). Turned out very nice. I made this one along with "Honey Gingerbread" and took both to work. Although I liked this one best, Honey Gingerbread was the overall favorite, six to three.

Rating: 4
